TEXT.3: again according to the timing and sequence above and summed for 10.24 seconds

TEXT.4: which is approximately one spacecraft rotation.  SOPA Key Parameters are

TEXT.5: normally averaged over three telescopes for ~ 1 minute (6 - 10.24 second

TEXT.6: data accumulation cycles) giving an average over much of the sky.  The time

TEXT.7: associated with each set of Key Parameters is determined by using the time

TEXT.8: (in minutes of the day) at the start of each data collection cycle as an index

TEXT.9: into an array of 1440 time slots dividing the day into 1440 one minute

TEXT.10: intervals.  The time reported is the midpoint of each interval.
